  </p>

  <p>
    The key difference between at-home masks and professional treatments is power output (measured in milliwatts per square centimeter). Clinical devices deliver 10–50 mW/cm², while most consumer masks deliver 5–15 mW/cm². Softer intensity means slower results, but the mechanism is identical.
  </p>

