  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-section">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>How long does each red light therapy session take?</strong>
      <p>Most sessions are 10–20 minutes. The mask's timer helps you stay consistent without overdoing it. Shorter sessions (10 min) are gentler for beginners; longer sessions (20 min) can be used 3–4x weekly for faster results.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Can you use red light therapy with serums?</strong>
      <p>Yes — applying a hyaluronic acid or vitamin C serum before your session can enhance absorption. Avoid retinol directly before LED use, as retinol can increase photosensitivity. Apply serum after the mask instead.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Is red light therapy safe for sensitive skin?</strong>
      <p>Red light is one of the gentlest wavelengths and doesn't cause UV damage. Most dermatologists consider it safe for all skin types, including sensitive skin. If you have active inflammation or compromised barrier, start with 10-minute sessions and increase gradually.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>How long until you see results from red light therapy?</strong>
      <p>Clinical studies show visible improvement in 4–8 weeks with consistent use 3–5 times per week. Subtle changes in skin texture may appear sooner (2–3 weeks), but measurable collagen improvement takes 8–12 weeks. Patience is essential.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Does this mask work on acne?</strong>
      <p>This mask focuses on red light (collagen/anti-aging). For acne, you'd want a mask that also includes blue light therapy at 415nm. Red light supports healing and reduces inflammation, so it's complementary to acne treatment but not primary.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

